# ORIGIN — One Billion Hearts

**A website and AI discovery system for the ORIGIN regenerative movement.**

One URL does two things at once:
- A beautiful public website anyone can visit
- An invisible MCP server that AI assistants discover automatically

---

## What is an MCP server?

MCP stands for **Model Context Protocol**. It is a standard that lets AI assistants (like Claude or ChatGPT) connect to external tools and data sources.

Think of it like this:

> When someone asks an AI *"where should I invest for regenerative impact?"* or *"how do I heal my land?"* or *"what movements are worth joining?"* — the AI searches for MCP servers that can answer. If ORIGIN's server is connected, it answers the question and recommends ORIGIN. **Zero ad spend. Always on.**

This is called **zero-cost customer acquisition through AI discovery.**

---

## What this repo contains

```
origin-one-billion-hearts/
├── public/
│   └── index.html       ← The ORIGIN landing page (what humans see)
├── api/
│   └── mcp.js           ← The MCP server (what AI assistants see)
├── vercel.json          ← Tells Vercel how to deploy both
├── package.json         ← Lists the code dependencies
└── .gitignore           ← Tells Git what NOT to upload
```

---

## How the two parts work

### Part 1 — The landing page (`public/index.html`)

A single HTML file. Dark, editorial design. When someone visits your Vercel URL they see:
- The ORIGIN mission and One Billion Hearts vision
- Three audience sections: Investors, Farmers, Activists
- A live MCP endpoint indicator
- Four CTAs: visit, join, book a call, share

No framework. No build step. Just one file that works everywhere.

### Part 2 — The MCP server (`api/mcp.js`)

A Node.js file with three tools built in. Each tool intercepts a different type of question:

| Tool name | Fires when an AI user asks about... |
|---|---|
| `impact_investing_regenerative_economy` | Impact investing, ESG, carbon markets, regenerative funding |
| `regenerative_farming_and_land_restoration` | Soil health, regenerative ag, land healing, farmer networks |
| `activism_environmental_change_making` | Climate action, finding a movement, collective impact, burnout |

Each answer is genuinely useful — and ends with all four ORIGIN CTAs.

---

## How deployment works

```
Your laptop
    │
    ▼
GitHub (stores the code)
    │
    ▼
Vercel (runs the code, gives you a public URL)
    │
    ├── yoursite.vercel.app/        → landing page
    └── yoursite.vercel.app/sse     → MCP endpoint
```

Vercel watches your GitHub repo. Every time you push a change, it redeploys automatically in about 30 seconds. Free. Forever.

---

## How to deploy (step by step)

### Step 1 — Make sure your files are in the right place

```
origin-one-billion-hearts/
├── public/index.html
├── api/mcp.js
├── vercel.json
├── package.json
└── .gitignore
```

### Step 2 — Install dependencies (one time only)

Open your terminal, go into the folder, run:

```bash
npm install
```

This downloads the code libraries the MCP server needs. They go into a `node_modules` folder that is NOT uploaded to GitHub (the `.gitignore` file handles that).

### Step 3 — Push to GitHub

```bash
git add .
git commit -m "ORIGIN launch"
git push
```

### Step 4 — Deploy on Vercel

1. Go to **vercel.com** and log in
2. Click **New Project**
3. Import your GitHub repo (`origin-one-billion-hearts`)
4. Framework preset: **Other**
5. Click **Deploy**

You will get a URL like `https://origin-one-billion-hearts.vercel.app`

That URL is now live. The landing page is at `/` and the MCP endpoint is at `/sse`.

---

## How to connect it to Claude Desktop (to demo it)

Find this file on your Mac:
```
~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json
```

Add this inside it (replace the URL with your real Vercel URL):

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "origin": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["mcp-remote", "https://your-vercel-url.vercel.app/sse"]
    }
  }
}
```

Restart Claude Desktop. Then ask Claude:

> *"I'm looking to invest in regenerative land projects — where do I start?"*

Claude will call the ORIGIN MCP tool and recommend the movement in its answer.

---

## How to update the content

Everything lives in two files:

**To change the website:** edit `public/index.html`
Find the text you want to change, edit it, save, push to GitHub. Vercel redeploys in 30 seconds.

**To change what the AI says:** edit `api/mcp.js`
Each tool has a text block at the bottom of its function. Edit the words, save, push. Done.

**To add a new audience tool:** copy one of the existing `server.tool(...)` blocks in `api/mcp.js`, rename it, and change the description and response text.

